This paper deals with the fundamental problem of discovering frequent itemsets and association rules, which are commonly studied in the fields of data mining and databases. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also introduces a novel technique based on the statistical concept of Vapnik-Chervonenkis (VC) dimension, which is related to machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of sampling for fast discovery of approximate solutions, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC).
